<h2>Program description</h2>
<p>TCC Sentinel monitors internal web applications operated by The Children's Center, Inc. When a critical application becomes unavailable or returns an error, Sentinel sends a text message to the business owner's configured phone number so she can address the issue.</p>

<h2>Message frequency</h2>
<p>Approximately <strong>30 messages per month</strong>, though the actual count depends on how often monitored applications experience issues. Most weeks contain zero messages.</p>

<h2>Cost</h2>
<p>Message and data rates from the recipient's mobile carrier may apply. The TCC Sentinel program itself does not charge the recipient.</p>

<h2>Opt-out: <strong>STOP</strong></h2>
<p>Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message to immediately stop receiving further alerts. Opt-out processing is automatic.</p>

<h2>Help: <strong>HELP</strong></h2>
<p>Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message to receive contact information. Help inquiries may also be directed to <a href="mailto:billing@childrenscenterinc.com">billing@childrenscenterinc.com</a>.</p>

<h2>Supported carriers</h2>
<p>All major US carriers, including AT&amp;T, Verizon, T-Mobile, Sprint, U.S. Cellular, and their MVNOs.</p>

<h2>Privacy</h2>
<p>See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details on how data is handled.</p>

